value.value: A mediastinal cancer that has_material_basis_in neural cells.
A globe disease that is characterized by inflammation of the inside of the eye.
A brain cancer that is located_in the infratentorial region.

A germ cell cancer that derives_from germ cells that are found in areas of the body other than the ovary or testicle. The tumors originate in the sperm forming cells in the testicles or egg producing cells in the ovary.
A malignant giant cell tumor that is composed_of multinucleated giant cells.

A brain disease that is characterized by low pressure inside the skull, and thus in the brain tissue and cerebrospinal fluid; may occur as a result of an occult or iatrogenically caused leak of CSF into another body cavity; may result in the downward displacement of the cerebellar tonsils through the foramen magnum or Chiari malformation; has_symptom orthostatic headache; other symptoms are related to compression of cranial nerves due to brain sagging.

A brain disease that is characterized by excess accumulation of fluid in the intracellular and/or extracellular spaces of the brain, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom blurred vision, has_symptom seizure, has_symptom coma.

A rhinitis which involves a hypersensitive reaction to various potentially irritating stimuli such as changes in weather, temperature, or barometric pressure, chemical irritants such as smoke, ozone, pollution, perfumes, and aerosol sprays, psychological stress and emotional shocks, medications, alcohol, and spicy food.

A rhinitis which involves inflammation of the nose characterized by atrophy of nasal mucosa including the glands, turbinate bones, and the nerve elements supplying the nose that is caused by heredity factors, endocrine imbalance, nutritional deficiency, bacterial infection and autoimmune issues.
A disease of mental health that involves physical symptoms suggesting a physical illness where the biological or medical cause of the symptoms is indeterminate.

A testicular cancer that has_material_basis_in the surface epithelium of the testis and is characterized by the presence of cysts lined by transitional cells and solid nests of transitional cells in a spindle cell stroma.
A mixed germ cell cancer that is located_in the testis.
A placenta disease that is characterized by an abnormally deep attachment of the placenta, through the endometrium and into the myometrium.
A sex cord-gonadal stromal tumor that is located_in the testis.
A breast benign neoplasm that is characterized by a collection of excess blood vessels.

An impotence that is characterized by an inability to achieve and maintain an erection due to defects in the arterial blood flow to the penis or a defect in venous occlusive function allowing blood drainage from the erectile tissue.
A lung cancer that has_material_basis_in tissues of the lung and has_material_basis_in pleural tissues. It is most commonly effects children.
A carcinosarcoma and embryonal cancer that is located_in embryonic tissue and results_in a mass of rapidly growing cells.
A pulmonary blastoma that derives_from the lung or pleural cavity.
A kidney cancer that is characterized by the presence of fibroblastic cells.
A Goodpasture syndrome that is characterized by damage to only kidney capillaries.
